.TH "phy_validate" 9 "phy_validate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
phy_validate \- Checks the phy parameters
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" phy_validate
.BI "(struct phy *phy "  ","
.BI "enum phy_mode mode "  ","
.BI "int submode "  ","
.BI "union phy_configure_opts *opts "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phy" 12
the phy returned by \fBphy_get\fP
.IP "mode" 12
phy_mode the configuration is applicable to.
.IP "submode" 12
PHY submode the configuration is applicable to.
.IP "opts" 12
Configuration to check
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Used to check that the current set of parameters can be handled by
the phy. Implementations are free to tune the parameters passed as
arguments if needed by some implementation detail or
constraints. It will not change any actual configuration of the
PHY, so calling it as many times as deemed fit will have no side
effect.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if successful, an negative error code otherwise
